<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     07-29 0431</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0444</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Rumble Over Dakotas</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms lingered today over the Midwest, hours after a
tornado touched down in New Mexico.
   Showers and thunderstorms extended this morning from western
Minnesota across southeastern North Dakota, South Dakota and
western Nebraska. Showers and thunderstorms also were scattered
over Montana, Arizona, New Mexico, southwest Texas, southwest
Louisiana, Florida and eastern North Carolina.
   In northern South Dakota, golf ball-size hail fell near Langford
and nearly 2 inches of rain fell during 20 minutes south of
Pierpont.
   A tornado touched down west of Las Cruces, N.M., but no damage
was reported.
   Heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included almost an inch at Aberdeen, S.D.
   Dozens of houses in Columbus, Ohio, were flooded after as much
as 3.5 inches of rain fell in about two hours early Friday.
   ``The water was all the way to the top of my basement steps,''
said Pam Seely as she and her neighbors dragged muddy and
water-soaked furniture out of their houses. ``Our refrigerator was
floating at the top of the stairs. My washer and dryer were
floating, our pool table.''
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms over
eastern Louisiana, Mississippi, Alabama, southwest Georgia, and
Florida; and scattered showers and thunderstorms over central
Arizona, southwest Utah and southern Nevada.
   Highs were expected to be in the 60s around San Francisco; in
the 70s over northern New England, inland New York, central and
western Pennsylvania, the Great Lakes, western Washington state,
the central and southern California coast and central Arizona; in
the 100s across the desert southwest and inland valleys of central
California; and in the 80s and 90s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 40
degrees at Marquette, Mich., to 91 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 76 hazy; Boston 64 fair; Buffalo 59 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 79 fair; Cincinnati 68 fair; Cleveland 66 hazy;
Detroit 58 smoke; Miami 79 partly cloudy; New York 68 fair;
Philadelphia 65 fair; Pittsburgh 60 fair; Portland, Maine 60 fair;
Washington 72 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 64 fair; Chicago 68 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
81 fair; Denver 68 fair; Des Moines 74 fair; Indianapolis 68 fair;
Kansas City 78 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 71 cloudy; Nashville 78
partly cloudy; New Orleans 77 hazy; St. Louis 77 partly cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 67 fair; Anchorage 61 showers; Las Vegas 89
fair; Los Angeles 62 foggy; Phoenix 92 fair; Salt Lake City 77
cloudy; San Diego 68 fair; San Francisco 57 partly cloudy; Seattle
65 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 54 fair; Toronto 57 fair.
</TEXT>
