<FIRST>r i AM-Philippines     07-29 0113</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Philippines,0115</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mother, Four Children Killed in Grenade Attack</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An unidentified assailant threw a
grenade at a home in the central Philippines, killing a mother and
her four children as they slept, a military report said Saturday.
   The attack took place late Friday on the outskirts of the town
of Masbate, 230 miles southeast of Manila, the Philippine
Constabulary report said.
   Anita Franco, 40, and her four boys, aged 12 to seven months,
died in their sleep, the report said. The father was not at home at
the time.
   The military said the killing may have been caused by a
longstanding feud, but the statement did not elaborate.
</TEXT>
