<FIRST>r i AM-Bangladesh-Sinkings     07-29 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Bangladesh-Sinkings,0167</SECOND>
<HEAD>57 Missing After Three Boats Sink</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A boat with 30 people bound for a
wedding sank during a rainstorm in the south, leaving 24 missing,
police said Saturday. The storm also sank two other boats, and 33
other people were reported missing.
   The boat with wedding guests capsized Friday in the Meghna River
while en route to the bride's village near Chandpur town, 40 miles
southeast of Dhaka, police said.
   Six people were rescued but the others aboard were feared
drowned, a police official said by telephone from Chandpur.
   A Bengali-language newspaper, Dainik Bangla, reported that two
fishing boats sank Friday in the Bay of Bengal off the town of
Cox's Bazaar 185 miles southeast of the capital.
   Bad weather was hampering the search for 33 missing fishermen,
the newspaper said.
   At least 50 people died Thursday when a double-deck ferry sank
after colliding with a cattle boat on the Panguchi River in
southern Bangladesh.
